RACE.RACE_TEXT: SAM HOUSTON RACE PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 11000. (PLUS UP TO $1,870 ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 16, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 115 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $6 ,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOWS N LACE settled back behind the field while saving ground on the backstretch, then was moving up on the far turn to rally from the four path down the stretch and was able to close the fastest to prevail in the end. NORA'S LEGACY chased the pace while two wide on the backstretch, was in a steady drive heading into the far turn to rally from the three path in the early stretch and closed well for the place prize. PAINTBRUSH stalked the pace down the backstretch while three wide, then vied for the lead on the far turn, shook free from the battling trio to lead the way into the stretch, but was out bid by outer rivals and was best for third place. SHESMYBROKER lead the way into the first turn to set the pace down the backstretch, faded throughout the far turn, then re bid again in the late stretch but came up empty. SHE'S FIRE AND ICE pressed the pace from the two path down the backstretch, then continued to move up to vie for the lead throughout the far turn, was used up and weakened in the late stretch. HIGH VALUE TARGET chased the pace under a steady drive down the backstretch and into the far turn to make a mild bid in the stretch then flattened out in the end. SUFFRAGETTE was unhurried early while four wide on the backstretch, then bid on the far turn and was no threat.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY BOY BLING was settled then raced three wide on the turn, rallied and was in a long drive in the stretch and bumped repeatedly with HARD OLD inside the furlong marker and proved best in the end. HARD GOLD was well placed while three wide into the turn, rallied on the turn and was four wide turning for home, dug in gamely then bumped repeatedly with MY BOY BLING inside the furlong marker then was out finished in deep stretch. FARM DOG set the early pace while inside, was hard used then faltered in the stretch drive. AMERICAN FOREST was settled while four wide on the backstretch, made a bid five wide to upper stretch but flattened out in the drive. LITTLE JONY was unhurried early then made a mild rally while three wide in the stretch and was no threat. MR. VALENTINO was unhurried early while inside into the turn and was no threat. HYPERION NORTH was pressing the pace while two wide into the turn, was in tight nearing the top of the stretch and stopped. A claim of foul was lodged by the rider of HARD GOLD against the rider of MY BOY BLING for interference in the stretch. A steward's inquiry was held concerning the running of the race. After reviewing the film's, there was no change to the order of finish.
